cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DS

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper is about a project that aims to facilitate porting source code and proofs between members of the HOL family of theorem provers, which are all based on logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the API component of the Common HOL Platform, which defines a standard interface for interacting with HOL systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the adaptation of legacy systems to conform to the Common HOL Platform, which involves software engineering techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the hand-translation of source code from one HOL system to another, which could potentially involve machine learning techniques. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the Common HOL Platform, which could involve data structures and algorithms.
